Most Asked Interview Questions
Q1. What is 1-Tier Architecture?

In 1-Tier Architecture, the user, application, and database reside on the same machine.

Q2. What is 2-Tier Architecture?

In 2-Tier Architecture, the client application directly communicates with the database server.

Q3. What is 3-Tier Architecture?

In 3-Tier Architecture, the client communicates with an application server, which communicates with the database server.

Q4. Which architecture is most used today?

3-Tier Architecture.

Q5. Why is 3-Tier better than 2-Tier?

Because it provides better security, scalability, maintainability, and centralized business logic.

